   {
      "body" : "Discussed on IRC:\r\n```\r\n<sipa> wumpus: if we need to fix the serialization for gettxoutsetinfo... maybe we can replace it with a merkleized version?\r\n<wumpus> sipa: you mean a 6-month masters project for someone? :) or isn't it that bad to do?\r\n<sipa> wumpus: i don't mean UTXO commitments\r\n<wumpus> ohh!\r\n<wumpus> sure, would be good to have a better format\r\n<wumpus> I'm everything but married to the current one, and apparently we already broke it once without anyone noticing, so (as long as we mention it in the release notes) I'm not against breaking it again\r\n<sipa> but we can iterate over the utxo entries in order like now, but use an incremental merkle tree hasher (similar to the algorithm used by ComputeMerkleRoot and friends now)\r\n<wumpus> cool\r\n<sipa> the overhead would be the same, and you could make it answer queries for specific entries... and it could later just be converted to a commitment structure\r\n<wumpus> yes, after  the memory improvement for the merkle tree hasher it doesn't have to store all the data in meory\r\n```\r\nI think this makes sense, as we'll have to break the compatibility anyway, let's use the opportunity to move to a better format.\r\n",
